PURPOSE:
	Currently sootbot projects all run as independent programs. No shared resources. I want a way to share resources
	across projects. I cannot toggle these projects as needed. There is also little in the way of formal command
	support, and I'd like to add this.
	The idea is a central repository which hosts a single main method. The main methods from other sootbot projects
	will be removed, and moved into a method which can be triggered from the central repository. This repository will
	include support for formal commands, and host shared resources such as settings for all servers (e.g. modlogs and mod roles),
	and shared methods such as isStaff.
	A command should have a label (i.e. name), a description, usage help, permission nodes, and some sort of scope (global, server-specific etc)
	Once the repository is ready, all projects should be made using the repository as a dependency. Each module should have things
	such as name, author, version and dependencies (other modules).
	See spigot for inspiration.
	
	in the final development stages, resources such as server-settings and bot token should be moved to an external file from
	the project, so that another dev may use the jar as a standalone and put their details into a file that I cannot see, and
	they cannot see my details. At the very end, I may even use my finished project to make an interactive site similar to
	dyno, to allow a dev to customise settings on my own multiguildnetwork.
	
REQUIRED TO RUN:

server settings should be placed in a JSON file, for now called guilds.json. Default values are provided if they are not
specified for a given guild:
	prefix: "^"
	modlogs: -1
	modrole: -1
	guild_id: -1
